# Types & Constants Conventions

## Types Organization

| File | Contains |
|------|----------|
| `types/models.ts` | Domain model interfaces (User, Group, Order, etc.) |
| `types/api.ts` | API request/response types, pagination types |
| `types/common.ts` | Utility types (Nullable, WithChildren, AsyncStatus) |
| `types/index.ts` | Re-exports everything |

Rules:
- Use `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions/aliases
- Use `import type` for type-only imports
- Prefix API types with purpose: `LoginRequest`, `UserListResponse`
- Module-specific types go in `modules/<feature>/types/`

## Constants Organization

| File | Contains |
|------|----------|
| `constants/routes.ts` | Route path strings |
| `constants/api.ts` | API endpoint paths and tag type strings |
| `constants/validation.ts` | Validation rules and messages |
| `constants/app.ts` | App-wide config (name, page size, debounce) |
| `constants/index.ts` | Re-exports everything |

Rules:
- Use `as const` on constant objects for literal types
- API endpoint functions for parameterized paths: `DETAIL: (id: string) => /items/${id}`
- Validation constants feed into zod schemas in `utils/validation.ts`
